 </code><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>Amends the Unified Code of Corrections. Provides if the defendant has </code><code>been found guilty by a judge or jury after a trial, the prosecutor shall </code><code>file with the court at the sentencing hearing a verified written statement </code><code>signed by the prosecutor setting forth the prosecutor's final offer, if </code><code>any,  of any  specified sentence and any charge to be dismissed or not </code><code>charged in a plea discussion in exchange for a plea of guilty from the </code><code>defendant and waiver of his or her right to trial. Also provides in any </code><code>sentence, a defendant shall not be punished by the imposition of a heavier </code><code>or greater sentence merely because he or she exercises his or her </code><code>constitutional right to be tried before an impartial judge or jury.</code><code>
